text: Božidar Delić (, ; 20 February 1956 – 23 August 2022) was a Serbian politician and general. From 2007 until his death, he was a member of the National Assembly of Serbia. He was the National Assembly Vice President from 2007 to 2012 and again from 2 August to 23 August 2022. Delić was born in Đakovica, then-FPR Yugoslavia. Delić died on 23 August 2022 at a hospital in Moscow, Russia from an illness at the age of 66. ==References== Category:1956 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Serbian politicians Category:Generals
